<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 6:15PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Jefferson County
through 645 PM EDT...
At 615 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Davisboro, or 8 miles
west of Louisville, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Louisville, Wrens, Stapleton, Avera, Matthews, Stellaville, Grange
and Stapletons Crossroads.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
